commit.message:
allow cythonized class's methods to be exposed

When a class is cythonized, its methods become
'cython_function_or_method' instead of 'function'.
Then both 'inspect.isfunction' and 'inspect.ismethod' returns False on
'cython_function_or_method', but 'inspect.ismethoddescriptor' seems to
return True.
See also https://github.com/irmen/Pyro4/pull/208 .
remove version specifics that might change anyway
